conbody.p:
We recommend the following setup procedure:


Log in as Admin (default password: Admin) ( );

Create a database ( );

Specify file name and path;

Specify school name, type, address, phone, URL, and contact information ( );

Define student body subdivision structure if necessary ( );

Save the database if deferred mode is active (see  );

Close database ( );

Open application settings window ( ) and set the following:


user interface language;

path to the database created earlier;

set deletion confirmations as necessary;

if necessary, set Deferred mode and Autosave modes and autosave interval;

Press OK;



Open account management window and create user accounts ( ).

Dialog Nibelung Student Manager is set up and ready. End users can now log in with their credentials and work with the database.
